### Wompi Payment Tests

### 1. Create Wompi Payment
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/wompi/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "wallpaperNumbers": [1, 5, 10],
  "buyerEmail": "test@example.com",
  "buyerName": "Juan Pérez",
  "buyerIdentificationNumber": "12345678",
  "buyerContactNumber": "3001234567",
  "amount": 45000
}

### 2. Create Single Wallpaper Payment
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/wompi/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "wallpaperNumbers": [7],
  "buyerEmail": "maria@test.com",
  "buyerName": "María González",
  "buyerIdentificationNumber": "87654321",
  "buyerContactNumber": "3109876543",
  "amount": 15000
}

### 3. Test Minimum Amount (should work)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/wompi/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "wallpaperNumbers": [1],
  "buyerEmail": "min@test.com",
  "buyerName": "Test Min",
  "buyerIdentificationNumber": "123456",
  "buyerContactNumber": "3001111111",
  "amount": 1000
}

### 4. Test Invalid Amount (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/wompi/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "wallpaperNumbers": [1],
  "buyerEmail": "invalid@test.com",
  "buyerName": "Test Invalid",
  "buyerIdentificationNumber": "123456",
  "buyerContactNumber": "3001111111",
  "amount": 500
}

### 5. Test Missing Fields (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/wompi/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "wallpaperNumbers": [1],
  "buyerEmail": "missing@test.com"
}

### 6. Test Invalid Email (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/wompi/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "wallpaperNumbers": [1],
  "buyerEmail": "invalid-email",
  "buyerName": "Test Email",
  "buyerIdentificationNumber": "123456",
  "buyerContactNumber": "3001111111",
  "amount": 15000
}

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:7071
